article.headline: VA Commonwealth 70, James Madison 43
article.story: HARRISONBURG, Va. (AP) -- Michael Doles scored 18 points and Nick George had 16 Monday night as Virginia Commonwealth avenged an embarrassing home loss to James Madison five days ago with a 70-43 thrashing of the Dukes. The Rams (11-8, 7-3 Colonial Athletic Association) won impressively for the second straight game. They beat CAA-leading Old Dominion 75-71 on Saturday in Richmond. James Madison (4-14, 2-8) beat the Rams 66-58 last Wednesday night, but trailed 14-4 after just 4:02 and never got the deficit into single digits again. Leading 39-28 at halftime, the Rams scored the first 12 points of the second half. Doles had the first 7 points in the run, George hit a 3-pointer and Jesse Pellot-Rosa's layup with 16:03 remaining made it 51-28. The Dukes never got closer than 20 again. Ray Barbosa led James Madison with 12 points and Chris Cathlin had 10. The Rams shot almost 59 percent, the Dukes under 38 percent.
